  "root_text": {
    "sn24.70:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 24.70 ",
    "sn24.70:0.2": "3. Tatiyagamanavagga ",
    "sn24.70:0.3": "Adukkhamasukhīsutta ",
    "sn24.70:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn24.70:1.2": "“Kismiṁ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṁ upādāya, kiṁ abhinivissa evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjati: ",
    "sn24.70:1.3": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti? ",
    "sn24.70:1.4": "“Bhagavaṁmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā …pe…. ",
    "sn24.70:2.1": "“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṁ upādāya, rūpaṁ abhinivissa evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjati: ",
    "sn24.70:2.2": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti. ",
    "sn24.70:2.3": "“Vedanāya sati …pe… ",
    "sn24.70:2.4": "saññāya sati … ",
    "sn24.70:2.5": "saṅkhāresu sati … ",
    "sn24.70:2.6": "viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṁ upādāya, viññāṇaṁ abhinivissa evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjati: ",
    "sn24.70:2.7": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’ti. ",
    "sn24.70:3.1": "Taṁ kiṁ maññatha, bhikkhave, ",
    "sn24.70:3.2": "rūpaṁ niccaṁ vā aniccaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn24.70:3.3": "“Aniccaṁ, bhante” …pe… vipariṇāmadhammaṁ, ",
    "sn24.70:3.4": "api nu taṁ anupādāya evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: ",
    "sn24.70:3.5": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti? ",
    "sn24.70:3.6": "“No hetaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn24.70:3.7": "“Iti kho, bhikkhave, yadaniccaṁ taṁ dukkhaṁ. ",
    "sn24.70:3.8": "Tasmiṁ sati, tadupādāya evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjati: ",
    "sn24.70:3.9": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti. ",
    "sn24.70:3.10": "“Vedanā …pe… ",
    "sn24.70:3.11": "saññā … ",
    "sn24.70:3.12": "saṅkhārā … ",
    "sn24.70:3.13": "viññāṇaṁ niccaṁ vā aniccaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn24.70:3.14": "“Aniccaṁ, bhante” …pe… vipariṇāmadhammaṁ, ",
    "sn24.70:3.15": "api nu taṁ anupādāya evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: ",
    "sn24.70:3.16": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti? ",
    "sn24.70:3.17": "“No hetaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn24.70:3.18": "“Iti kho, bhikkhave, yadaniccaṁ taṁ dukkhaṁ. ",
    "sn24.70:3.19": "Tasmiṁ sati, tadupādāya evaṁ diṭṭhi uppajjati: ",
    "sn24.70:3.20": "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṁ maraṇā’”ti. ",
    "sn24.70:3.21": "Chabbīsatimaṁ. ",
    "sn24.70:3.22": "Tatiyapeyyālo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn24.70:0.1": "Linked Discourses 24.70 ",
    "sn24.70:0.2": "3. The Third Round ",
    "sn24.70:0.3": "The Self Is Neither Happy Nor Suffering ",
    "sn24.70:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn24.70:1.2": "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise: ",
    "sn24.70:1.3": "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and healthy after death’?” ",
    "sn24.70:1.4": "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” ",
    "sn24.70:2.1": "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises: ",
    "sn24.70:2.2": "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is healthy after death.’ ",
    "sn24.70:2.3": "When feeling … ",
    "sn24.70:2.4": "perception … ",
    "sn24.70:2.5": "choices … ",
    "sn24.70:2.6": "consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises: ",
    "sn24.70:2.7": "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and healthy after death.’ ",
    "sn24.70:3.1": "What do you think, mendicants? ",
    "sn24.70:3.2": "Is form permanent or impermanent?” ",
    "sn24.70:3.3": "“Impermanent, sir.” … ",
    "sn24.70:3.4": "",
    "sn24.70:3.5": "",
    "sn24.70:3.6": "",
    "sn24.70:3.7": "“And so, what’s impermanent is suffering. ",
    "sn24.70:3.8": "When this exists, grasping at this, the view arises: ",
    "sn24.70:3.9": "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is healthy after death.’ ",
    "sn24.70:3.10": "Is feeling … ",
    "sn24.70:3.11": "perception … ",
    "sn24.70:3.12": "choices … ",
    "sn24.70:3.13": "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” ",
    "sn24.70:3.14": "“Impermanent, sir.” … ",
    "sn24.70:3.15": "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?” ",
    "sn24.70:3.16": "",
    "sn24.70:3.17": "“No, sir.” ",
    "sn24.70:3.18": "“And so, what’s impermanent is suffering. ",
    "sn24.70:3.19": "When this exists, grasping at this, the view arises: ",
    "sn24.70:3.20": "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and healthy after death.’” ",
    "sn24.70:3.21": ""
  },
